 Is Complicated : Steinar's Uneasy Co-existence of Tourism and Petroleum in the Lofoten-Vesterålen Archipelago / Ashley Barrett and Hindertje Hoarau-Heemstra -- The Progress Party in the Summer of Horror / Matthew B. Morris -- Norwegian vs. U.S. Prisons : A Sister's Reflections / Brittany L. Peterson -- The Norwegian Workplace Hustle : A Crisis of Shifting National Identity / Ashley Barrett and Dawna Ballard -- It is Hard to be Suave When You Fish for Cod : Belonging, Identity, and the Future in Norway / Nick A. Merola -- Norway under Attack / Melissa Murphy and Maegan Stephens -- Doubly Disadvantaged : Ethnic and Gender Bias in Norway's Engineering Sector / Matt McGlone -- The Indian Bride Who Became the Deputy-Mayor of Røst / Preeti Mudliar -- First Female Mayor Strikes Largest Oil Deal for Dying Hammerfest / Caroline Sinclair -- The Petroleum Renaissance in Alstahaug Municipality / Krister Salamonsen -- Epilogue : Characters Solve the Complication: Writing about Culture / Madeline Maxwell.  a"The discovery, just forty years ago, of vast oil and gas reserves in Norway's Arctic High North region created an economic titan. This original research illustrates the many challenges and opportunities now facing Norway's citizens in a region which the government has designated its top strategic priority. An ethnographic study, the book showcases interviews with 21 representative individuals from the area and reveals the various impacts petroleum development has on their regional economy and culture"--cProvided by publisher.  a29 0aPetroleum industry and tradexSocial aspectszNorway, Northern. 0aPetroleum industry and tradexEnvironmental aspectszNorway, Northern. 0aEthnologyzNorway, Northern. 0aNorway, NorthernxSocial conditions. 0aNorway, NorthernxEnvironmental conditions.1 aSørnes, Jan-Oddvar,eeditor of compilation.1 aBrowning, Larry D.,eeditor of compilation.1 aHenriksen, Jan Terje,eeditor of compilation.  aHD9575 .N62 C85 2015hGMCT-OS-B